sentences: Albert Floyd Piccirilli (July 13, 1928 – May 24, 2020), also known by his stage name Al Rex, was an American bass player for Bill Haley & His Comets and its predecessor Bill Haley and the Saddlemen.
He started playing for them in 1949 and became noted for "wild antics" on stage.
He formed his own band, Al Rex and the Regaleers in 1960.
On May 24, 2020, he died in his Norristown, Pennsylvania home from pneumonia.
He appeared as a member of the band in the 1950s films Rock Around the Clock (1956) and Don't Knock the Rock (1957).
